# TypeScript Conventions

## Variables & Types

- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Provide explicit types for function parameters and return values
- Use interfaces for object shapes; use types for unions/intersections

## Functions

- Use arrow functions for callbacks
- Use async/await over raw Promises
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Keep functions pure when possible

## Imports

- Use ES modules (import/export)
- Group imports: external, then internal, then relative
- Use absolute imports when configured

## React (if applicable)

- Use functional components with hooks
- Keep components small and focused
- Use TypeScript for props (no PropTypes)
- Prefer controlled components

## Error Handling

- Use try/catch for async operations
- Create custom error types when needed
- Never catch and ignore errors

## Formatting

- Use Prettier for consistent formatting
- Keep lines under 100 characters
- Use consistent semicolons (prefer with)
